@The_Outsider wrote:

jr fizzy:

if you get an error after what the outsider said above me then it means you need to take your java files out of the (x86) file and put them into the normal program files then change the compiler so that it’s not searching in the (x86) files that should fix the error if you get one from what the outsider said. allthough it’s unlikely you will get the error.

So long as you call to the right directory and have the Environment Variables set the same, it shouldn’t matter.
